<content>
<para id="fs-idm1398224240">
Keith,<newline/><newline/>

It has been such a joy working with you over the years. From the time when we were both in RCA, to working with you as our liaison for OpenStax, and most recently working with you in OpenStax; it has alway been a great experience. 
<newline/><newline/>
I was truly surprised, honored, and thrilled when you informed me that you wanted to be considered for the Associate Director position in OpenStax. Having your presence in the office over these past couple of years has been so warming, and I’m not quite sure how we’ll get by after you decide to leave us. I hope you’ll visit us every so often and update us all on your travels and activities in retirement. Truly wishing you the best retirement ever! 

Very best regards,<newline/><newline/>
Beth</para>
  <para id="delete_me">Keith,<newline/><newline/>
 
I hope you have come to trust me and know that I will take your secrets to my <term>grave</term>.  Best of luck!  It was a great pleasure knowing and working with you.<newline/><newline/>
 
Love always,<newline/><newline/>
 
Adela.</para>

<note id="fs-idm463709040" class="astronomy seeing-for-yourself"><title>Keithians</title>
<para id="fs-idm402534864">We’re all <term>Keithians</term>. - Roy Johnson</para></note>

<figure id="fs-idm809913856">
<media id="fs-idm866341312" alt="Alt test for Art Asset">
<image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/baby.JPG"/>
</media>
<caption>Lauren's baby shower</caption>
</figure> 

<para id="eip-439">Keith! Congratulations on making it through this last chapter of your working life. You’re bright personality and charming wit have made OpenStax a better place to work for a lot of people — me included! The way you help people without making them (me) feel dumb about asking for help is pretty great.
<newline/>
I hope you get to thoroughly enjoy your retirement. And you can always come back to the old IBC bank building when you’re bored and want to remember what it’s like to be a working stiff. Capiche? - Carly</para><para id="fs-idm878384704">favorite <term>Keith-ism</term>: swerving, tire screeching sound effects when you're trying to pass each other in a hallway - Micaela McGlone</para>

<para id="fs-idm868461024">Keith, <newline/><newline/>
Thank you for all your years in <term>RCA</term>.  I really appreciated your commitment to the staff to ensure they were trained and supported in their work.  I especially remember your willingness to participate in the on-campus training sessions.  Additionally, you became a wonderful source of guidance for the administrators and faculty members who came to rely on you for your knowledge of their awards. Your accounting experience in both industry and at Rice was invaluable when we were charged with reviewing and documenting the internal controls required under Uniform Guidance. <newline/><newline/>
I am sure your years at <term>OpenStax</term> were likewise appreciated. <newline/><newline/> 
Rice will miss you.  Don’t forget us – keep in touch.  But above all, ENJOY YOUR RETIREMENT!<newline/><newline/>
Terry<newline/><newline/>
P.S. I still remember your untiring efforts to lead RCA in on-key singing of Happy Birthday.</para>

 <figure id="fs-idm1563020080">
