<caption>2016 Summer</caption></figure><para id="eip-63">Dear Keith, happy retirement! Best wishes to you and your family. I hope you have an amazing and happy time getting to relax, spend time with family, and travel the world! Congrats! -Theresa</para><list id="eip-129"><title>Things Phil Schatz Slacked to Larissa</title><item>I don’t see him often but every time I visit he’s always happy &amp; chatty (if you start) no matter the time of day. </item>
<item>I hope you continue spreading joy to everyone you meet</item>
<item>Keith: What Santa’s elves aspire to be</item></list><para id="eip-575">Thank you for being puzzled by the Monday Punday with me and thank you for helping me figure it out when I’m puzzled alone. I will miss you, Keith! - Britt Weinstein</para><para id="eip-311">greatest and most relaxing wishes upon your release from the indenture of capitalism! - ryan</para><para id="eip-318">Enjoy your retirement! I hope you see amazing things around the wold with your family. - Colby</para><para id="eip-215">Hey Keith!<newline/>
We are going to miss seeing you around the office for sure. I am so happy that you get to spend all your time with your family :heart:. It has been a pleasure working with you for as long as I have been here. You are so kind and thoughtful. You are an awesome person. Thank you for being patient with me as I bugged you with questions and CS favors. Hope you get to relax and enjoy your retirement :). <newline/>
Much Love,<newline/>
Meera</para>

<para id="eip-246">Best wishes on your retirement!  I enjoyed working with you in RCA.<newline/>
Julie Goodfriend</para><para id="fs-idm612067024">Keith,<newline/><newline/>

It was a pleasure working with you in research &amp; cost accounting. I hope you enjoy your next chapter in life. May your new journey be filled with joy!<newline/><newline/>

Congratulations,<newline/>

Roxie Romer</para><para id="eip-293">Keith,<newline/><newline/>

It has been my pleasure to work with you.  We have the same work anniversary April 1st. I am inspired by the terrific career you have had.  I wish you a happy retirement.  I will miss you and your leadership.<newline/><newline/> 

Lina Nguyen (RCA)</para>

<para id="fs-idm1032948512">Bon voyage Keith!  I know you have exciting travels ahead of you getting to those last few states!  It has been a pleasure working with you both as my supervisor and mentor, and as our OpenStax liaison.  Please don’t be a stranger and come visit us in RCA for lunch whenever you can.<newline/><newline/>

Take care!<newline/><newline/>

Sandy Tanner</para>

<para id="fs-idm1102241280">Morning conversations with Keith, as part of the "old-men club" always start my day off on a cheerful note.  Somehow, we manage to avoid drifting into "get of my lawn" grumpy-isms. Not sure how I'm going to remember to get tickets for Chamber Music Houston tickets without his reminders! - Ross</para>

<para id="fs-idm1401335904">Keith, thank you so much for your friendship.  You are the exemplar of what quiet professionalism looks like, and I can only hope to be as wise someday.  I hope retirement treats you well and you manage to travel north with stops to see us occasionally!  You and your family will always be welcome here. (Nathan &amp; Holly Stitt)</para>

<para id="fs-idm345071136">Keith, You've been such a wonderful colleague and part of the OpenStax team. You've brought a lot of fun and positive energy to our organization and I will miss you immensely. - Nicole</para></content>

